Package: sirwls
Type: Package
Title: Sliced Inverse Regression via Weighted Leverage Score (SIR-WLS)
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Nadia", "Asrir", email = "n.asrir@ump.ac.ma", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Abdallah", "Mkhadri", role = "aut"))
Description: Implements SIR-WLS, the sliced inverse regression via weighted
    leverage score estimator of Asrir and Mkhadri (2025)
    <doi:10.1080/00949655.2025.2550340>: a model-free weighted leverage
    score (Zhong et al. 2012) screens predictors from the singular value
    decomposition of the design matrix, classical sliced inverse regression
    is then applied to the screened subset, and the resulting direction is
    extended with zeros for the unselected predictors. Also provides a plain
    Lasso baseline, the proximity criterion and variable-selection accuracy
    metrics (TPR, FPR, FDR) used in the paper's empirical study, and a
    correlated-Gaussian data simulator matching its simulation design.
